Xishuangbanna, one of China's largest tropical rain forest reserves, will almost double its area to bring more wild plants and animals under protection.
The province has limited the number of trees to be chopped down in the forest area in northwest Yunnan and has stopped building sugar factories in the Xishuangbanna region to preserve the only tropical rain forest in the country located there.Northwest China's Yunnan Province
The Academy of Sciences has observation posts in the Xishuangbanna region to study the bio-diversity and scientists have moved 3,000 rare plants to a special 90-ha area for protection.
